Resolves #643, test cases failed due to global state in CallsCount (#803) * Resolves #643, test cases failed due to presence of global state in CallsCount. Because AppTest was executed before B2BServiceTest, it scheduled 1 sec timer using ThrottleTimerImpl class. While resetting it used that global CallCount class reset() method, which reset all counters. So that causes thread safety issue because of unintended sharing of application state between test cases, which is not a good practice.

1) Refactored LotteryNumbers to use Joiner from guava library to join lottery numbers. 2) Solved potential thread safety issue in LotteryTicketId class, where it was using raw primitive value and incrementing it which is not thread-safe. As getAll method returns a Stream, we cannot close the involved resources (Connection, Statement and resultSet) until the stream is closed by the consumer. So try-with-resources is not an option as per sonarqube’s recommendation. But it is still recommended to close statement and result set. When connection pool used, connection is not closed when close() called. It is just returned to the pool. Using //NOSONAR to avoid false blocker issue.
